NOTES :

Selenium locators :
1. ID
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "id_of_element")
2. XPATH
    driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "xpath")
3. CSS SELECTORS
    driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "CSS Selectors")
4. CLASSNAME
    driver.find_element(By.CLASS_NAME, "class_of_element")
5. NAME
    driver.find_element(By.NAME, "name_of_element")
6. LINKTEXT
    driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, "Text of Link")
7. PARTIAL LINK TEXT
    driver.find_element(By.PARTIAL_LINK_TEXT, "Text of Link")
8. TAGNAME
    driver.find_element(By.TAG_NAME, "Tag name")

Formula for xpath :
//tagname[@attribute="value"]

Formula for CSS selector :
tagname[attribute = "value"]

STATIC DROPDOWN : Dropdown values remain fixed.
AUTO SUGGESTIVE DROPDOWN : Dropdown values change wrt inputs.

**static dropdown is used when a select tag is present and we have select class.

dropdown = select(driver.find_element(By.ID,"xyz"))
dropdown.select_by_index(0)
dropdown.select_by_visible_text("Female")
dropdown.select_by_value("value")

AUTO SUGGESTIVE DROPDOWNS :

We cannot hardcode popups , so we need to loop in the options.
Get access to all elements in the dropdown.

countries = driver.find_elements(By.CSS_selector,"li[class="ui_menu_item]a")
print(len(countries))
for country in countries :
    if country.text == "India":
        country.click()
        break